  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/5589",
  "title": "useRefinementList: eslint fails with error \"Avoid referencing unbound methods which may cause unintentional scoping of this\"",
  "body": "### 🐛 Current behavior\n\nWhen using `useRefinementList` as per [documentation](https://www.algolia.com/doc/api-reference/widgets/refinement-list/react-hooks/#hook) there is `@typescript-eslint` error:\r\n```\r\nAvoid referencing unbound methods which may cause unintentional scoping of `this`\r\n```\n\n### 🔍 Steps to reproduce\n\n1. enable [@typescript-eslint/recommended-requiring-type-checking](https://typescript-eslint.io/linting/configs#recommended-requiring-type-checking) in the project\r\n2. use the following code:\r\n    ```ts\r\n   const { refine } = useRefinementList({ attribute: 'brand' });\r\n    ```\r\n3. run eslint and see output:\r\n    ```\r\n    Error: Avoid referencing unbound methods which may cause unintentional scoping of `this`.\r\n    If your function does not access `this`, you can annotate it with `this: void`, or consider using an arrow function instead.  @typescript-eslint/unbound-method\r\n    ```\n\n### Live reproduction\n\nhttps://codesandbox.io/embed/heuristic-chihiro-f2nv7x?fontsize=14&hidenavigation=1&theme=dark\n\n### 💭 Expected behavior\n\nEslint check pass\n\n### Package version\n\nalgoliasearch 4.16.0 react-instantsearch-hooks-web 6.42.0\n\n### Operating system\n\nmacOS 13.1\n\n### Browser\n\nChrome/112.0.0.0\n\n### Code of Conduct\n\n- [X] I agree to follow this project's Code of Conduct",
